Source: wlanpi-shell-config
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Josh Schmelzle <josh@joshschmelzle.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: wlanpi-shell-config
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, vim, tmux, bash-completion
Recommends: fzf, xclip
Description: Professional shell configuration for WLAN Pi
 Provides optimized vim, tmux, and bash configurations for network
 professionals. Includes:
  * Enhanced tmux with WiFi monitoring status bar
  * Professional vim setup with leader key bindings
  * Comprehensive bash aliases for system administration
  * Large history buffer and improved history management
  * Terminal title support for tmux sessions
 .
 These configurations are designed for network engineers and provide
 a consistent, powerful shell environment across all WLAN Pi devices.
